bioghist.head: College of Business, Self-Evaluation and Accreditation Files
bioghist.p: The School of Business and Economics was established by the Board of Trustees of CWSC on August 5, 1974. President Brooks, believed the college was a necessary addition to the Central, “whose time had come.” In 2001, the SBE recommended that name be changed to College of Business (COB). In 2008, the COB changed its name to CB.

scopecontent.p: The collection contains the Self-evaluation, and accreditation reports from the College of Business during the years between 1980-2013. It also contains portraits fo faculty, staff, and administraters from 1973-2018

arrangement.p: The collection is split into five series. The first contains self-evaluation reports. The second series contains ephemera and newsletters. The third series is called 3D objects. It contains audio tapes and display boards. The fourth series contains documents about the accreditation process for the CWU College of Business. The fifth series is photographic portraits.

accessrestrict.p: Open to the public for research.

controlaccess.p: This collection is indexed under the following headings in the online catalog. Researchers desiring materials about related topics, persons, or places should search the catalog using these headings.
